d gay rights activist\n|-\n|33||Dr Mukul Kr Sarma|| LGBT activist, has written several pieces in the ''[[The Assam Tribune]]'' in an effort to raise awareness of LGBT people and mobilise the LGBT community in Assam\n|-\n|34||[[Vikram Seth]]|| Writer\n|-\n|35||[[Parmesh Shahani]]|| Author\n|-\n|36||[[Gopi Shankar Madurai]] || [[Genderqueer]] activist, recipient of the [[Commonwealth of Nations|Commonwealth]] Youth Worker Asia Finalist Award and founder of [[Srishti Madurai]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/intersex-person-to-contest-from-madurai-north/article8539185.ece|title=Intersex person to contest from Madurai North|date=30 April 2016|publisher=|newspaper=The Hindu|last1=Reporter|first1=Staff}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/elections-2016/tamil-nadu-elections-2016/news/3rd-gender-gets-a-new-champion-in-Tamil-Nadu-poll-ring/articleshow/51935940.cms|title=3rd gender gets a new champion in Tamil Nadu poll ring - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Intersex-candidate-alleges-harassment/articleshow/52197962.cms|title=Intersex candidate alleges harassment - Times of India|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/intersex-person-contesting-tn-polls-ze-wants-change-your-mind-sexual-minorities-42103|title=This intersex person is contesting TN polls, 'ze' wants to change your mind on sexual minorities|date=24 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n|37||[[Parvez Sharma]]|| Writer and documentary filmmaker\n|-\n|38||[[Manvendra Singh Gohil]]|| Hereditary Prince of Rajpipla\n|-\n|39||[[Ramchandra Siras]]|| Linguist and author\n|-\n|40||[[Living Smile Vidya]] || Actor, artist, writer, and theater activist \n|-\n|41||[[Kalki Subramaniam]]|| Transgender activist, actor, artist, writer and founder of [[Sahodari Foundation]]\n|-\n|42||[[Manil Suri]]|| Indian-American mathematician and writer\n|-\n|43||[[S. Swapna]]|| First transwoman to clear [[Tamil Nadu Public Service Commission]] exam and first transgender I.A.S aspirant\n|-\n|44||[[Laxmi Narayan Tripathi]]|| Transgender activist\n|-\n|45||[[Ruth Vanita]]|| Writer and academician\n|-\n|46||[[Abhinav Vats]]|| Equal rights activist and India's first openly gay actor; featured in a music video from [[Euphoria (Indian band)|Euphoria]] in 1996 in a first ever gay character shown on Indian media\n|-\n|47||[[Rose Venkatesan]]|| First transgender TV host in India\n|-\n|48||[[Riyad Vinci Wadia]]|| Filmmaker\n|}\n\n== Summary table ==\n{{LGBT rights summary\n| legality = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] (Since 2018)<br/> \n| equal_aoc = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] (Since 2018)<ref name=\"bbc\"/>\n| antidiscrimination = \n| antidiscrimination_employment = [[File: Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]/[[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Only extends to discrimination from the state or government bodies)\n| antidiscrimination_goods = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]\n| antidiscrimination_genderid = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]\n| antidiscrimination_other = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]/[[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Only extends to discrimination from the state or government bodies)\n| hate crimes law including sexual orientation and gender identity = \n| hate speech law including sexual orientation and gender identity = \n| marriage = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Proposed) \n| recognition = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Proposed)\n| step_adoption = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Proposed)\n| single_adoption = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]\n| joint_adoption = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Proposed)\n| military_service = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Pending)<ref name=\"military\">{{cite news |last1=Dutta |first1=Amrita |title=Indian Army is worried now that men can legally have sex with other men |url=https://theprint.in/security/indian-army-is-worried-now-that-men-can-legally-have-sex-with-other-men/113644|work=The Print |date=7 September 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"military1\">{{cite news |title=Parliament winter session: Bills seek ban on non-veg food at official events, rights to LGBT to serve in armed forces|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2018/dec/28/parliament-winter-session-bills-seek-ban-on-non-veg-food-at-official-events-rights-to-lgbt-to-serv-1917748.amp|work=The New Indian Express |date=28 December 2018}}</ref>\n| gender_change = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] (Since 2014; sex reassignment surgery required since 2019)<ref>{{cite news |title=Transgender Person Act passed in Parliament|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/despite-massive-protests-trans-bill-gets-president-s-assent-becomes-law-113643}}</ref>\n| conversion_therapy = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]]\n| intersex_surgeries = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]/[[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Banned in Tamil Nadu)<ref name=\"Live Law.in\"/><ref name=\"The News Minute\"/><ref name=\"The Times of India\"/><ref name=\"Kyle Knight - Human Rights Watch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2019/08/29/indian-state-bans-unnecessary-surgery-intersex-children|title=Indian State Bans Unnecessary Surgery on Intersex Children - Human Rights Watch|accessdate=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref name=\"Human Rights Watch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2019/04/29/indian-court-decides-favor-informed-consent-rights-intersex-people|title=Indian Court Decides In Favor of Informed Consent Rights for Intersex People - Human Rights Watch|accessdate=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n| reassignment surgery = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] (Since 2014)\n| third_gender = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] (Since 2014)\n| Automatic parenthood = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Proposed) \n| homosexuality_declassified = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]\n| ivf_access = [[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Radha |first=Sharma |title=IVF bundle of 'Anand' for US lesbian couple |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/IVF-bundle-of-Anand-for-US-lesbian-couple/articleshow/45085039.cms |work=The Times of India |date=9 November 2014}}</ref>\n| anti-bullying = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] \n| surrogacy = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]] (Explicit ban pending regardless of sexual orientation)<ref>{{cite news |title=Surrogacy Regulation Bill Passed In Lok Sabha: 10 Points|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/surrogacy-regulation-bill-passed-in-lok-sabha-10-points-1965215|work=NDTV |date=19 December 2018}}</ref> \n| blood_donation = [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Power |first1=Shannon |title=No LGBTI person can donate blood in India\n|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/no-lgbti-person-can-donate-blood-india|work=GayStarNews |date=20 July 2017}}</ref>\n| other_title1 = \n| other1 = \n| other_title2 =\n| other2 = \n}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Human rights in India]]\n* [[LGBT rights in Asia]]\n* [[LGBT culture in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{LGBT in India}}\n{{Asia topic|LGBT rights in}}\n{{India topics}}\n{{Social issues in India}}\n\n[[Category:LGBT rights in India]]\n[[Category:LGBT rights in Asia]]\n[[Category:Human rights in India]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTransgender rights:Typo fixing, replaced: An other  \u2192 Another", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_India"}
